data.description: Boy, oh boy! Have we got the house for you! This is not your average Forest Hills home. This well loved, custom built home is looking for its new owners to come in and give it the refresh it deserves. Meticulously maintained and cared for by the original owners, just bring your vision and creativity! You'll feel like you are escaping into your own reality entering through the stone clad front porch. Enter into a spacious foyer that features neutral tile flooring. the home flows effortlessly from room to room. The living room is large and bright thanks to the large bay window. Into the formal dining room, you will find it to be perfect for evening dinners, or holiday gatherings with a pass through buffet counter into the kitchen. The seller advised that the wall between the dining room and kitchen is not load bearing and could be opened up for a more open layout. The kitchen was way ahead of it's time for when the home was built. Boasting a large center island with range in the middle, tons of cabinet and counter space, a dishwasher, trash compactor, and garbage disposal, the layout is ideal for any cook! There is a large step down family room off the kitchen that features sliding glass doors to your sunroom that overlooks your backyard oasis. The main level is completed by a powder room and access to your attached 2 car garage. Upstairs you first find a huge primary suite that features double door entry, his and hers closets, and a large primary bathroom with extra large vanity with double sinks and a stall shower. There are 3 more good sized bedrooms and a large full hall bath with double sinks and tubshower. There is a full unfinished basement that houses the laundry and is begging to be finished to create more living space. The backyard is truly the crown jewel of the property. with a large deck that connects directly to your sprawling patio where you can sun bathe or take a dip in your in ground pool! there is also a side yard with a play area. This home can be your dream home with just a few cosmetic updates. The roof is only 7yo, HVAC was replaced in 2018, and the hot water heater was replaced in 2017. The property is being sold strictly in its as-is condition with all inspections for informational purposes only. Any and all repairs and certifications, including the certificate of occupancy, will be the sole responsibility of the buyer and at the buyer's own expense. Homes similar to this in Williamstown, completely updated, have been selling for over $450,000. With a little bit of sweat equity (or a 203K loan) you could have your dream home!
